-- Sharp says small, mid-size panel orders lower than expected
-- 
-- Fri Feb 1, 2013 1:42am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/02/01/us-sharp-earnings-panel-idUSBRE91009J20130201

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Japan's Sharp Corp ( 6753.T ) said orders for small and medium size panels for smartphones came in below expectations. But television sales improved, a company executive said on Friday. 
 Sharp reported a rebound to an operating profit in the third quarter, improving the bailed-out consumer electronics maker's chances of convincing lenders and shareholders that it is a viable company. (Reporting by Reiji Murai)